face*25. Or, 'perils such as our strength can bear;' or 'perils which are enough to daunt us.'

moment*26. Cp. i. 10 med., and 21.

glory*27. Or, taking tychès with kairou: 'while for a moment in the hands of fortune, at the height, not of terror but of glory, they passed away.'

afterwards*28. Or, taking lôphesanta with spasmon: 'these convulsions in some cases soon abated, in others not until long afterwards.'

