admiral*47. Cp. ii. 66.

night*48. Or, reading aphormisamenoi, 'they had weighed anchor before it was light, but had been detected.'

beginners*49. Cp. i. 142.

us*50. Or, taking the antecedent to hô as supplied by the clause hou di' allo ti tharsousin... katorthountes: 'as to the ground of the confidence with which they attack us as if courage were native to them.'

